WEBVTT

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:20.940
=About Love=

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.940
=Episode 12=

00:01:29.790 --> 00:01:31.200
Once upon a time,

00:01:31.790 --> 00:01:33.710
there was a boy and a girl.

00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:37.680
The boy was the girl's perfect prince.

00:01:38.350 --> 00:01:41.120
And the girl was his ideal princess.

00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:45.480
They were truly made for each other.

00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:47.920
Until they grew up,

00:01:48.560 --> 00:01:49.430
and got together…

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:55.000
Why won't you let me
send the photo to Yu?

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:58.280
Just because Xiu is your friend?

00:01:58.870 --> 00:02:00.000
Do you know

00:02:00.480 --> 00:02:01.480
the consequences of this?

00:02:02.590 --> 00:02:03.430
I do.

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:05.000
Yu will be free from suffering.

00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:07.590
How do you know it's suffering

00:02:08.470 --> 00:02:10.430
and not the darkness before dawn?

00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:12.080
It's up to

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:13.080
Yu to decide.

00:02:13.680 --> 00:02:15.310
You're not related to Yu,

00:02:15.560 --> 00:02:17.080
but you don't want her to be deceived.

00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:19.030
So you chose to tell her the truth.

00:02:19.330 --> 00:02:20.430
That shows how kind you are.

00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:22.400
No need to say that.

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:25.080
Just get to the "but."

00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:25.960
There is no "but."

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:27.910
Who dares to say their past

00:02:27.930 --> 00:02:29.800
is innocent and flawless?

00:02:30.370 --> 00:02:31.430
That everything they've done

00:02:31.910 --> 00:02:33.280
can be laid out in the open,

00:02:33.490 --> 00:02:34.590
fit to see the light of day?

00:02:37.250 --> 00:02:39.120
Maybe the biggest difference
between us and Xiu

00:02:39.960 --> 00:02:41.470
is that his flaws are out in the open.

00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:44.560
This man's

00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:47.280
words sound reasonable,
but they're twisted.

00:02:47.740 --> 00:02:49.240
He doesn't distinguish between genders

00:02:49.560 --> 00:02:50.800
or call out crimes.

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:52.750
If everyone is guilty,

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.150
that naturally includes you.

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:55.840
And if you're guilty,

00:02:56.120 --> 00:02:58.080
what right do you have to accuse me?

00:03:00.560 --> 00:03:01.750
So...

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:04.870
Everyone has secrets.

00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:07.680
Whoever sees through
the other's secrets first

00:03:08.240 --> 00:03:10.630
can handle things more calmly.

00:03:11.120 --> 00:03:12.190
Exactly.

00:03:13.150 --> 00:03:15.240
Maybe I'm burdened with countless sins,

00:03:15.870 --> 00:03:17.910
and sooner or later I'll be judged.

00:03:18.840 --> 00:03:20.430
But I don't think that's a bad thing.

00:03:21.080 --> 00:03:22.430
It's more like a kind of release.

00:03:24.030 --> 00:03:24.870
Who knows?

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:26.680
Maybe someone will set me free soon.

00:03:27.870 --> 00:03:29.240
Once, a little boy

00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:31.000
ran to me crying.

00:03:31.630 --> 00:03:32.680
He said

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:34.560
his dad cheated on his mom,

00:03:35.470 --> 00:03:36.590
and he was in so much pain.

00:03:37.710 --> 00:03:38.960
He didn't know what to do.

00:03:39.310 --> 00:03:40.150
I asked if he

00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:41.520
wanted to tell his mom.

00:03:41.710 --> 00:03:42.560
He said yes,

00:03:43.030 --> 00:03:45.190
but he was scared of losing his family.

00:03:45.310 --> 00:03:46.400
It's a trap.

00:03:46.710 --> 00:03:48.590
He's using role reversal

00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:50.240
to make others empathize

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:52.630
and plant seeds of self-doubt.

00:03:54.680 --> 00:03:55.680
I asked

00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:57.470
if he'd feel guilty

00:03:58.590 --> 00:04:00.590
knowing his mom was deceived

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:02.520
because he didn't tell her.

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:05.360
He said yes.

00:04:05.710 --> 00:04:07.150
For a child,

00:04:07.910 --> 00:04:09.910
they all want a complete,
harmonious family.

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:13.750
Telling his mom would mean

00:04:13.750 --> 00:04:15.270
paying a huge price.

00:04:15.400 --> 00:04:17.120
Either his parents divorce,

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:20.240
or the family falls apart.

00:04:20.720 --> 00:04:22.190
Either way, it's painful.

00:04:23.430 --> 00:04:25.070
Keeping the family whole

00:04:25.360 --> 00:04:27.390
at least hurts the child less.

00:04:28.120 --> 00:04:29.830
So the key question is

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:32.270
who will he sacrifice?

00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:35.510
It seems like an emotional dilemma,

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:37.920
but it's actually a moral interrogation.

00:04:38.600 --> 00:04:39.440
Clever.

00:04:40.870 --> 00:04:42.510
What did the little boy choose?

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:45.040
What would you do

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:46.560
if you were him?

00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:56.950
I don't know.

00:04:58.310 --> 00:05:00.070
From the child's perspective,

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:01.800
he had no choice.

00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:03.310
But he couldn't say anything.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.830
Otherwise, he'd be wrong no matter what.

00:05:09.360 --> 00:05:10.630
Are you telling me this story

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:13.190
to lower my moral standards?

00:05:14.560 --> 00:05:16.070
Then you don't know me well enough.

00:05:17.630 --> 00:05:19.070
I treat everyone equally.

00:05:20.360 --> 00:05:21.630
Few people can betray

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:22.800
their own family for justice.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.190
So that means most people are wrong.

00:05:27.390 --> 00:05:29.360
Did you make up that boy's story?

00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:30.680
It's real.

00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:33.190
Later, his mom

00:05:33.830 --> 00:05:34.800
found out the truth,

00:05:35.270 --> 00:05:36.270
and chose to leave.

00:05:37.360 --> 00:05:38.630
His dad was

00:05:38.920 --> 00:05:39.950
consumed by regret,

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:42.000
and the little boy

00:05:42.750 --> 00:05:43.800
lost his home.

00:05:46.190 --> 00:05:48.310
So you think that's the worst outcome?

00:05:49.270 --> 00:05:51.390
For Yu and Xiu to have a better outcome,

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:53.190
I should stay silent.

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:55.120
I just don't think

00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:57.160
we should play hero
in the name of

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:58.630
"doing what's right."

00:05:59.310 --> 00:06:00.150
If

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:02.390
you had evidence of
every cheater in the world,

00:06:03.190 --> 00:06:04.070
what would you do?

00:06:04.510 --> 00:06:05.350
If I could,

00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:07.040
I'd make it my job

00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:08.600
to let everyone know the truth.

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:10.750
Exposing the truth

00:06:11.070 --> 00:06:13.800
is no less than
starting a medium-scale war.

00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:17.720
Is covering up problems true peace?

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:20.000
If that's the case,

00:06:20.680 --> 00:06:22.000
I guess I'll have to give up this year's

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:23.390
Nobel Peace Prize.

00:06:25.480 --> 00:06:27.120
Today I finally saw your

00:06:27.120 --> 00:06:28.310
sharp-tongued side.

00:06:28.560 --> 00:06:29.750
No, I'm bad with words.

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:31.600
Actually, I'm not someone

00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:32.560
who ignores right and wrong.

00:06:33.070 --> 00:06:34.560
I just have hope for them.

00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:36.310
Hope that years from now,

00:06:36.430 --> 00:06:37.480
they'll still be together.

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:39.840
Who are they?

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:41.750
Yu and Xiu.

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:42.880
Oh.

00:06:44.040 --> 00:06:45.600
I hope by then,

00:06:45.950 --> 00:06:47.870
they'll be more mature
and more tolerant.

00:06:48.120 --> 00:06:49.800
And able to forgive
their reckless youth.

00:06:50.950 --> 00:06:52.120
To be with each other,

00:06:52.310 --> 00:06:53.270
face every trial,

00:06:53.920 --> 00:06:54.800
and keep walking forward.

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.800
But I don't want to
go through such trials,

00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:00.390
nor tolerate people who disrespect love.

00:07:01.510 --> 00:07:02.630
Call me picky about emotions.

00:07:02.680 --> 00:07:03.920
Plus diva syndrome.

00:07:07.570 --> 00:07:09.120
Stop pretending to be
the perfect nice guy.

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.310
Going all out to protect your friends

00:07:13.070 --> 00:07:14.240
doesn't make you look cool at all.

00:07:16.480 --> 00:07:17.320
Sorry.

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:19.750
No need to apologize.

00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:22.190
It's normal to speak up for a friend.

00:07:22.920 --> 00:07:24.190
But I really hope

00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:26.630
your attitude is out of loyalty,

00:07:27.040 --> 00:07:28.160
not just rigid principles.

00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:29.440
I do hope

00:07:29.480 --> 00:07:30.750
you stay away from Xiu's mess,

00:07:31.420 --> 00:07:32.290
but I'm not sure

00:07:32.290 --> 00:07:33.480
if I'm doing the right thing.

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:35.680
I just hope everyone

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:37.040
can have a good outcome

00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:38.400
and come to a good end.

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:41.720
I thought you'd be like me,

00:07:42.100 --> 00:07:43.630
stay out of others' domestic troubles.

00:07:44.270 --> 00:07:45.160
But you

00:07:45.560 --> 00:07:47.830
fearlessly insist

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:49.190
on doing what you think is right.

00:07:50.060 --> 00:07:51.560
I actually really like that about you.

00:07:55.400 --> 00:07:57.270
Does this count as
choosing love over friendship?

00:07:58.070 --> 00:07:59.750
I've done my best for my friends,

00:08:00.360 --> 00:08:01.390
but for you,

00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:03.270
I want to try harder.

00:08:11.510 --> 00:08:12.480
Marry me.

00:08:13.950 --> 00:08:14.790
What?

00:08:15.750 --> 00:08:16.590
I said,

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:18.680
marry me.

00:08:20.120 --> 00:08:21.630
I'm a little overwhelmed. I…

00:08:21.830 --> 00:08:22.670
No, I know.

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:24.950
I know the timing's a bit off.

00:08:25.240 --> 00:08:27.430
Luckily, the timing and place
are perfect.

00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:28.640
Unless

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.750
you'd rather jump in the river
than say yes.

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.270
Let me take a wild guess.

00:08:37.270 --> 00:08:39.030
Are you using this

00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:40.910
as hush money?

00:08:41.440 --> 00:08:42.480
Of course not.

00:08:42.670 --> 00:08:43.870
This is a proposal.

00:08:44.630 --> 00:08:46.030
Not a forced marriage.

00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:48.670
Actually, I brought you here today

00:08:49.790 --> 00:08:51.150
just to do this.

00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:53.480
But we ended up
talking about others first.

00:08:53.480 --> 00:08:54.320
So...

00:08:56.440 --> 00:08:57.280
So,

00:08:59.550 --> 00:09:00.790
will you marry me?

00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:02.600
Stand up first, then we talk.

00:09:02.750 --> 00:09:04.200
I need to show my sincerity.

00:09:04.790 --> 00:09:05.960
Just give me an answer.

00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:17.840
You know what?

00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:22.080
This feels like a distant dream.

00:09:22.870 --> 00:09:24.480
Like I've been

00:09:25.080 --> 00:09:26.440
waiting for this day
for a long time.

00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:28.560
Sorry.

00:09:30.120 --> 00:09:31.200
I'm late.

00:09:31.670 --> 00:09:33.200
I want to say yes right away,

00:09:36.030 --> 00:09:37.120
but I can't right now.

00:09:40.630 --> 00:09:41.470
Why?

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.440
Because you don't know me well enough.

00:09:51.790 --> 00:09:52.630
Got it.

00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:55.510
I guess

00:09:56.960 --> 00:09:58.320
what I said earlier

00:09:58.440 --> 00:10:00.000
changed your opinion of me.

00:10:01.120 --> 00:10:01.960
So

00:10:02.270 --> 00:10:03.670
you think you don't know me well?

00:10:03.720 --> 00:10:04.560
Right?

00:10:04.910 --> 00:10:06.960
If that's how you see it, it's fine.

00:10:08.330 --> 00:10:10.030
Getting to know each other
goes both ways,

00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:14.360
but that doesn't stop me
from loving you.

00:10:15.360 --> 00:10:16.550
To be unreserved,

00:10:17.480 --> 00:10:19.320
I'm dead set on marrying you.

00:10:21.570 --> 00:10:23.020
Don't regret it when the time comes.

00:10:23.020 --> 00:10:27.580
♪So I'm waiting♪

00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:29.240
I've been watching entertainment news
for 30 years.

00:10:29.240 --> 00:10:30.080
Never seen

00:10:30.100 --> 00:10:31.270
a proposal fail.

00:10:31.510 --> 00:10:32.720
If they're still together,

00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:34.600
they're heading for marriage anyway.

00:10:35.550 --> 00:10:36.390
You seem upset.

00:10:38.440 --> 00:10:39.360
No, I'm not.

00:10:40.080 --> 00:10:41.480
I was just thinking,

00:10:42.630 --> 00:10:45.750
how can we get to
know each other better?

00:10:48.150 --> 00:10:49.320
Are you free tomorrow?

00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:51.510
Yeah, what's up?

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:53.360
Come help me move.

00:10:54.360 --> 00:10:55.200
Move where?

00:10:56.150 --> 00:10:57.240
To your place.

00:11:03.150 --> 00:11:04.150
Welcome home.

00:11:05.380 --> 00:11:08.300
♪I♪

00:11:08.580 --> 00:11:17.020
♪I don't really wanna
look over my shoulder♪

00:11:18.860 --> 00:11:22.380
♪I♪

00:11:22.460 --> 00:11:29.940
♪I don't really mind to
wait till I'm older♪

00:11:33.670 --> 00:11:35.000
That's kinda sweet.

00:11:35.270 --> 00:11:36.110
Mm.

00:11:36.550 --> 00:11:37.670
No twist at all.

00:11:37.790 --> 00:11:39.480
I thought it'd end badly.

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:41.790
Is that a problem? I like it.

00:11:43.750 --> 00:11:45.720
If this scene happened to you,

00:11:46.480 --> 00:11:47.630
would you feel the same

00:11:51.510 --> 00:11:53.900
(If this really happened to me,)

00:11:54.420 --> 00:11:56.820
♪I♪

00:11:56.840 --> 00:11:59.670
(I'd definitely feel so happy.)

00:12:09.320 --> 00:12:10.200
I think

00:12:10.670 --> 00:12:12.120
movies aren't real.

00:12:13.120 --> 00:12:14.600
Writers can make

00:12:14.960 --> 00:12:16.080
characters perfect.

00:12:16.750 --> 00:12:18.270
But reality is cruel.

00:12:19.720 --> 00:12:20.960
You sound so pessimistic.

00:12:21.360 --> 00:12:22.510
In real life,

00:12:22.550 --> 00:12:24.440
that guy might send flirty messages

00:12:24.440 --> 00:12:26.000
behind his girlfriend's back,

00:12:26.720 --> 00:12:28.550
or meet another girl secretly

00:12:28.840 --> 00:12:30.360
after dropping his girlfriend home.

00:12:31.030 --> 00:12:32.720
Are all the guys you've met like that?

00:12:34.390 --> 00:12:35.230
Most of them.

00:12:38.270 --> 00:12:39.110
I remember

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:41.390
once when I was a kid,
I was watching Animal Planet.

00:12:41.670 --> 00:12:43.840
A jaguar caught a wild boar,

00:12:44.510 --> 00:12:45.870
but the boar escaped by luck.

00:12:46.910 --> 00:12:47.960
I actually felt relieved.

00:12:48.550 --> 00:12:50.840
But then something shocking happened.

00:12:51.240 --> 00:12:52.080
What did you see?

00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:53.480
As the boar

00:12:53.630 --> 00:12:54.600
ran for its life,

00:12:54.600 --> 00:12:56.360
its intestines fell out
all over the place.

00:12:58.320 --> 00:12:59.870
Ew, that's gross.

00:13:00.630 --> 00:13:01.510
Sorry

00:13:01.630 --> 00:13:02.470
I didn't know.

00:13:04.270 --> 00:13:05.510
I was terrified too.

00:13:06.150 --> 00:13:07.440
But my dad said,

00:13:07.720 --> 00:13:08.840
"Don't pity the boar,

00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:10.160
just like

00:13:10.320 --> 00:13:12.510
you can't pity the meat on your plate."

00:13:13.440 --> 00:13:15.000
Cheetahs hunt to survive.

00:13:16.200 --> 00:13:18.630
I thought it was cruel back then,

00:13:19.670 --> 00:13:20.910
but later I learned

00:13:21.080 --> 00:13:22.750
that to survive in the nature,

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:25.440
animals follow the law of the fittest,

00:13:25.600 --> 00:13:27.080
constantly adapting and evolving.

00:13:27.080 --> 00:13:28.510
We shouldn't question why cheetahs

00:13:28.510 --> 00:13:29.600
are so cruel,

00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.360
just like we shouldn't question

00:13:31.360 --> 00:13:33.120
the problems
that exist objectively in reality.

00:13:34.320 --> 00:13:35.200
Are you saying

00:13:35.200 --> 00:13:37.600
men being unfaithful
is an objective fact?

00:13:38.440 --> 00:13:39.670
You don't trust men,

00:13:40.510 --> 00:13:41.790
because none of the ones you've met

00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:43.390
are worth trusting.

00:13:43.400 --> 00:13:44.240
In other words,

00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:46.000
you think it's men's instinct.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:46.840
Right?

00:13:49.670 --> 00:13:51.120
This is Morita therapy.

00:13:53.510 --> 00:13:54.600
You know quite a lot.

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:57.150
Honestly, I don't ask for much.

00:13:58.360 --> 00:14:00.120
I just want to meet a man

00:14:00.260 --> 00:14:01.270
who can love his woman

00:14:01.270 --> 00:14:02.960
wholeheartedly.

00:14:03.550 --> 00:14:04.750
Then I'll believe

00:14:05.030 --> 00:14:06.030
men cheating isn't

00:14:06.030 --> 00:14:07.750
just how things are.

00:14:08.550 --> 00:14:10.200
Maybe it's just my own stereotype.

00:14:10.840 --> 00:14:12.720
So you need someone

00:14:12.790 --> 00:14:14.600
who can give you hope?

00:14:15.510 --> 00:14:16.720
If such a man exists,

00:14:16.720 --> 00:14:18.120
why doesn't he step up?

00:14:19.720 --> 00:14:22.200
I've met quite a few good men.

00:14:25.750 --> 00:14:26.750
So, Dr. Lin,

00:14:28.030 --> 00:14:29.320
are you a good man?

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:36.600
We've been talking about
men's nature so long,

00:14:36.600 --> 00:14:38.440
and now we're back to me.

00:14:39.790 --> 00:14:41.120
If the person comforting you

00:14:41.120 --> 00:14:43.200
is the kind you hate,

00:14:43.870 --> 00:14:45.960
then my words mean nothing.

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:50.510
The tricky part is

00:14:50.960 --> 00:14:52.360
saying I'm a good man

00:14:52.480 --> 00:14:53.720
means nothing.

00:14:54.320 --> 00:14:55.440
You can prove it.

00:15:01.720 --> 00:15:03.440
Should I take that as

00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:05.960
you wanting to test me?

00:15:09.750 --> 00:15:11.910
If you have doubts,

00:15:12.600 --> 00:15:14.120
you can choose not to take the test.

00:15:14.790 --> 00:15:16.960
Just go with
whatever feels right for you.

00:15:24.630 --> 00:15:25.870
How do you know

00:15:26.870 --> 00:15:28.320
I'm really attracted to you?

00:15:29.480 --> 00:15:31.550
Can't I tell if someone's

00:15:33.030 --> 00:15:34.480
truly into me?

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:37.200
What if I still can't

00:15:37.200 --> 00:15:39.150
give you hope in the end?

00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:43.630
That's not my problem to worry about.

00:15:45.320 --> 00:15:46.600
So how long will the test last?

00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:49.670
Weeks? Three to five months?

00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:51.840
One week.

00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:55.150
Looks like I might have a shot.

00:15:56.750 --> 00:15:58.270
I know you're not like the others.

00:15:58.600 --> 00:16:00.360
You study psychology,
read people's minds.

00:16:00.440 --> 00:16:01.720
More rational than most.

00:16:02.080 --> 00:16:03.390
You won't be easily controlled

00:16:03.440 --> 00:16:04.510
by emotions or desires.

00:16:06.630 --> 00:16:08.240
So during this trial period,

00:16:08.480 --> 00:16:09.440
what do I need to do?

00:16:09.790 --> 00:16:10.720
Let me think.

00:16:13.510 --> 00:16:15.150
First, meet every day.

00:16:15.720 --> 00:16:17.390
I'll choose the time and place.

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:18.840
Got it.

00:16:20.750 --> 00:16:21.670
Second,

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:24.270
treat me like your friend.

00:16:26.510 --> 00:16:27.960
Fair enough. What else?

00:16:28.910 --> 00:16:30.230
- Third,
- Don't worry.

00:16:30.960 --> 00:16:32.120
I know this is a test.

00:16:32.360 --> 00:16:33.480
I'll be polite.

00:16:34.670 --> 00:16:35.870
I'll contact you tomorrow.

00:16:36.320 --> 00:16:37.160
Okay.

00:16:37.550 --> 00:16:38.390
Miss Chen.

00:16:38.720 --> 00:16:39.960
If it's a weekday,

00:16:40.150 --> 00:16:41.840
I'm only free after 4 PM.

00:16:42.630 --> 00:16:43.600
Got it.

00:16:44.900 --> 00:16:46.240
Stop calling me Miss Chen from now on.

00:16:48.120 --> 00:16:48.960
Okay.

00:16:50.200 --> 00:16:51.150
Chen Qing.

00:16:58.200 --> 00:17:00.150
You have fewer things than I thought.

00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:02.360
Well, what about those bottles
in the bathroom?

00:17:02.360 --> 00:17:03.200
Taking them?

00:17:04.590 --> 00:17:06.240
Leave them. In case we argue,

00:17:06.350 --> 00:17:07.190
I might come back.

00:17:08.590 --> 00:17:10.030
You won't get that chance.

00:17:15.400 --> 00:17:16.240
Mm.

00:17:17.720 --> 00:17:18.560
Are you taking this?

00:17:19.830 --> 00:17:20.670
No.

00:17:21.030 --> 00:17:22.480
It's just a broken music box.

00:17:23.090 --> 00:17:23.950
Oh.

00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:24.880
I'll go put it away.

00:17:32.720 --> 00:17:33.750
What's all this?

00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:38.480
Don't look.

00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:40.400
I bought it ages ago.

00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:41.550
From my edgy teen days.

00:17:48.030 --> 00:17:48.870
What's wrong?

00:17:51.310 --> 00:17:52.400
I think they suit you.

00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:53.270
Wanna try?

00:17:53.290 --> 00:17:54.150
- Hey!
- Wait.

00:17:54.200 --> 00:17:55.270
You're so annoying.

00:17:55.270 --> 00:17:56.200
How come I never noticed

00:17:56.200 --> 00:17:57.310
you're such a tease before?

00:17:58.030 --> 00:17:59.240
Too late to regret it now.

00:18:09.060 --> 00:18:11.620
(Pu Shu: Those Flowers,
Quietly blooming for me)

00:18:11.990 --> 00:18:14.470
♪In the vast crowd♪

00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:16.560
What's up?

00:18:18.720 --> 00:18:19.680
I bet you

00:18:19.680 --> 00:18:21.240
I bet you haven't updated your playlist

00:18:24.030 --> 00:18:25.110
in at least ten years.

00:18:25.110 --> 00:18:27.070
The old songs still hit differently.

00:18:28.570 --> 00:18:31.960
♪Go our separate ways♪

00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:33.000
What's wrong with the car?

00:18:33.680 --> 00:18:34.920
Nothing, it's just…

00:18:34.920 --> 00:18:36.070
hasn't been serviced in ages.

00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:37.400
I'll fix it later.

00:18:39.110 --> 00:18:40.350
Why not drive mine?

00:18:40.350 --> 00:18:41.510
I don't like driving anyway.

00:18:41.880 --> 00:18:42.720
No need.

00:18:45.270 --> 00:18:46.550
I'm used to this one.

00:18:46.830 --> 00:18:48.510
Driven it for years, it's fine.

00:18:54.960 --> 00:18:55.800
Then

00:18:56.030 --> 00:18:57.720
update my playlist first.

00:18:57.720 --> 00:19:01.650
♪They've been carried away by the wind♪

00:19:01.650 --> 00:19:04.620
♪Scattered across the world♪

00:19:04.620 --> 00:19:07.340
(A Ray of Light in the Dark)

00:19:07.340 --> 00:19:09.930
♪I'll admit♪

00:19:09.940 --> 00:19:13.970
♪My back is faced against the wall♪

00:19:14.860 --> 00:19:18.370
♪There's nothing
that I wouldn't try to do♪

00:19:18.380 --> 00:19:22.930
♪For this feeling to have you♪

00:19:23.220 --> 00:19:26.650
♪I'll resist your gaze♪

00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:29.930
♪Your lips, your touches again♪

00:19:30.820 --> 00:19:34.170
♪There's no one
that I wouldn't try to fool♪

00:19:34.520 --> 00:19:37.850
♪For an image of you♪

00:19:39.080 --> 00:19:40.990
♪Take my hand again♪

00:19:41.160 --> 00:19:42.910
♪Take my mind again♪

00:19:43.130 --> 00:19:46.350
♪Break into my heart again♪

00:19:46.840 --> 00:19:48.810
♪I'm falling out again♪

00:19:48.820 --> 00:19:50.930
♪I'm on my knees again♪

00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:54.770
♪To beg for the truth♪

00:19:56.310 --> 00:19:59.050
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:19:59.070 --> 00:19:59.910
Come on.

00:20:00.310 --> 00:20:01.270
Uh... I... I don't...

00:20:01.270 --> 00:20:02.310
I don't eat duck blood.

00:20:03.110 --> 00:20:03.950
Just try it.

00:20:07.270 --> 00:20:08.200
Then have some meat.

00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:11.750
Is this lamb? I can't eat lamb.

00:20:11.750 --> 00:20:12.920
I can't stand the smell.

00:20:13.160 --> 00:20:14.310
Relax, it's not gamey.

00:20:14.310 --> 00:20:15.150
Try it

00:20:16.310 --> 00:20:21.120
♪Is it a push or a shove?♪

00:20:21.730 --> 00:20:24.520
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing♪

00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:25.800
Seems alright.

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:27.590
It's okay.

00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:28.800
Hm.

00:20:30.680 --> 00:20:31.640
Have some more then.

00:20:33.200 --> 00:20:34.040
Here.

00:20:35.660 --> 00:20:39.170
♪There's nothing
that I wouldn't try to do♪

00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:46.130
♪For this feeling to have you♪

00:20:46.910 --> 00:20:51.000
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:20:51.150 --> 00:20:56.330
♪Is that the secret to love?♪

00:20:56.660 --> 00:20:59.690
♪I thought it had came from below us♪

00:20:59.690 --> 00:21:02.970
♪Did it come from above?♪

00:21:02.970 --> 00:21:06.990
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:21:07.120 --> 00:21:12.290
♪Is it a push or a shove?♪

00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:15.690
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing♪

00:21:15.690 --> 00:21:19.440
♪This secret of love♪

00:21:21.480 --> 00:21:22.400
Dr. Lin.

00:21:24.750 --> 00:21:25.590
You're here.

00:21:26.920 --> 00:21:28.070
Play billiards often?

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:29.880
Haven't played in ages.

00:21:30.640 --> 00:21:31.480
Let's play a round.

00:21:32.030 --> 00:21:32.870
Okay.

00:21:45.240 --> 00:21:46.160
You break first.

00:21:46.720 --> 00:21:47.560
Okay.

00:21:53.920 --> 00:21:54.760
Do you play often?

00:21:55.070 --> 00:21:56.000
Not really.

00:21:56.510 --> 00:21:57.550
Just enjoy it.

00:21:58.550 --> 00:21:59.830
Playing requires focus.

00:22:00.240 --> 00:22:01.960
It calms you down slowly.

00:22:03.640 --> 00:22:05.270
Wanna make a bet?

00:22:10.070 --> 00:22:10.910
Bet on what?

00:22:11.070 --> 00:22:12.000
Whoever wins

00:22:12.310 --> 00:22:13.150
chooses

00:22:13.400 --> 00:22:14.830
the next meeting place.

00:22:15.310 --> 00:22:16.150
How does that sound?

00:22:16.270 --> 00:22:17.640
Sounds good,

00:22:18.070 --> 00:22:19.110
but I want to change it.

00:22:19.350 --> 00:22:20.550
What if we bet on

00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:23.240
the last meeting place instead?

00:22:23.730 --> 00:22:25.310
Looks like you already
have something in mind.

00:22:25.920 --> 00:22:26.760
Is that okay?

00:22:27.310 --> 00:22:28.150
Sure.

00:22:28.150 --> 00:22:29.000
Whoever wins

00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:30.590
picks the last meeting place.

00:22:31.110 --> 00:22:31.950
Deal.

00:22:43.240 --> 00:22:44.400
I was

00:22:44.510 --> 00:22:45.720
obsessed with billiards for a while.

00:22:51.030 --> 00:22:53.400
Calculating, planning, controlling.

00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:56.240
Every collision is predictable.

00:22:57.200 --> 00:22:58.200
The calmer you are,

00:22:58.830 --> 00:22:59.750
the more accurate you get.

00:23:05.720 --> 00:23:06.790
It's a battle of mindset.

00:23:07.160 --> 00:23:08.240
Whoever wavers first

00:23:08.680 --> 00:23:09.640
loses.

00:23:12.830 --> 00:23:14.310
It's off… just a bit.

00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:15.640
So close.

00:23:17.510 --> 00:23:18.680
I thought you were a rookie,

00:23:18.680 --> 00:23:19.590
turns out you're a pro.

00:23:20.200 --> 00:23:22.270
If I don't go all in,
I might actually lose.

00:23:23.030 --> 00:23:23.870
Come on.

00:23:52.310 --> 00:23:53.240
Impressive.

00:23:53.550 --> 00:23:55.510
I'm really curious. Can you tell me now?

00:23:55.960 --> 00:23:57.680
Where's the last meeting place?

00:23:59.830 --> 00:24:00.670
I haven't decided yet.

00:24:00.920 --> 00:24:01.830
You look so serious.

00:24:01.830 --> 00:24:03.680
I thought it meant something special.

00:24:04.030 --> 00:24:05.070
Got my hopes up for nothing.

00:24:05.440 --> 00:24:06.480
It does mean something.

00:24:06.790 --> 00:24:08.070
I just can't tell you right now.

00:24:09.510 --> 00:24:10.350
Alright.

00:24:10.410 --> 00:24:11.350
I'll go with your plan.

00:24:14.850 --> 00:24:16.590
I'm gonna take a call.
It's too noisy here.

00:24:16.720 --> 00:24:17.560
Okay.

00:24:27.790 --> 00:24:28.630
Hello.

00:24:39.140 --> 00:24:41.620
(Bei)

00:24:42.780 --> 00:24:43.960
(What do you want for dinner?)

00:25:17.960 --> 00:25:19.070
- Xiaoxi.
- Ah!

00:25:19.090 --> 00:25:20.110
You scared me to death.

00:25:20.400 --> 00:25:21.320
What's wrong with you?

00:25:21.960 --> 00:25:22.800
I thought...

00:25:23.640 --> 00:25:25.000
I thought someone was following me.

00:25:26.110 --> 00:25:26.950
Following you.

00:25:28.110 --> 00:25:30.400
It's fine.
Probably just sleep-deprived these days.

00:25:31.880 --> 00:25:32.920
Come on, let's head home.

00:25:33.590 --> 00:25:34.710
- Mm.
- Okay.

00:25:40.440 --> 00:25:41.510
Why'd you come down?

00:25:41.830 --> 00:25:42.750
To pick you up, of course.

00:25:57.920 --> 00:25:59.940
(Like.)

00:26:13.240 --> 00:26:14.080
Bei.

00:26:14.400 --> 00:26:15.240
Mm?

00:26:15.640 --> 00:26:16.550
Your phone's ringing.

00:26:25.020 --> 00:26:27.820
(An Miu: Like.)

00:26:35.240 --> 00:26:36.120
Mm.

00:26:36.240 --> 00:26:37.080
Look.

00:26:38.270 --> 00:26:39.130
Who is it?

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:40.680
That sister I told you about.

00:26:42.030 --> 00:26:44.160
Are you free
the day after tomorrow afternoon?

00:26:44.350 --> 00:26:45.440
Let's have afternoon tea.

00:26:45.880 --> 00:26:47.000
I'll introduce you two.

00:26:47.480 --> 00:26:48.440
The day after tomorrow?

00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:51.040
Alright.

00:26:52.160 --> 00:26:53.590
Okay, I'll tell her.

00:26:56.160 --> 00:26:58.590
Let's have afternoon tea
the day after tomorrow.

00:26:59.000 --> 00:27:00.480
I'll go with my girlfriend.

00:27:02.100 --> 00:27:03.980
(Lin Chen)

00:27:04.030 --> 00:27:04.870
(See you tomorrow)

00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:11.270
So, I'll pick you up

00:27:11.620 --> 00:27:12.590
the afternoon after tomorrow.

00:27:13.880 --> 00:27:14.720
Mm?

00:27:15.750 --> 00:27:17.270
No need, just send me the address.

00:27:17.440 --> 00:27:18.280
I'll go alone.

00:27:20.720 --> 00:27:21.560
What?

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:22.920
You smell so good.

00:27:24.690 --> 00:27:26.200
I used a new body wash I just bought.

00:27:26.880 --> 00:27:28.160
Yeah, I've got some

00:27:28.160 --> 00:27:29.790
cherry blossom chocolates
chilling in the fridge.

00:27:29.870 --> 00:27:30.740
Don't forget to eat it.

00:27:30.790 --> 00:27:31.960
You bought more?

00:27:32.160 --> 00:27:33.680
Haven't finished the last batch.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:35.110
What? Sick of it?

00:27:36.350 --> 00:27:39.310
No, wasting if we can't finish.

00:27:40.440 --> 00:27:42.830
You love it, so I bought more.

00:27:43.750 --> 00:27:45.000
How do you know I love it?

00:27:45.920 --> 00:27:46.920
You don't?

00:27:47.160 --> 00:27:48.030
First time you came over,

00:27:48.030 --> 00:27:49.270
you ate three boxes in one go.

00:27:50.510 --> 00:27:51.510
That's because there were

00:27:51.510 --> 00:27:53.240
no other flavors
in your cabinet, okay?

00:27:54.680 --> 00:27:56.720
But I really do love the sakura flavor.

00:27:58.960 --> 00:28:00.000
I ate three boxes,

00:28:00.000 --> 00:28:02.440
because I was shy.

00:28:03.030 --> 00:28:04.480
Shy? What's there to be shy about?

00:28:04.590 --> 00:28:05.640
I was nervous.

00:28:05.920 --> 00:28:06.760
Nervous?

00:28:07.880 --> 00:28:08.880
Scared I'd eat you?

00:28:09.590 --> 00:28:10.880
Scared I'd eat you.

00:28:13.480 --> 00:28:14.320
Then go ahead.

00:28:27.960 --> 00:28:29.030
Open it and see.

00:28:30.350 --> 00:28:31.240
What's this?

00:28:31.880 --> 00:28:32.830
It's for you.

00:28:34.680 --> 00:28:35.520
Do you like it?

00:28:39.880 --> 00:28:40.880
Is this appropriate?

00:28:41.110 --> 00:28:43.110
I bought it because
I thought it suits you.

00:28:43.560 --> 00:28:44.430
Yeah.

00:28:44.440 --> 00:28:46.310
I... I actually think it suits me too.

00:28:46.350 --> 00:28:47.510
I like it too, but...

00:28:49.070 --> 00:28:51.110
Isn't this a test?

00:28:51.110 --> 00:28:52.880
Why are you giving gifts?
I can't take it.

00:28:53.240 --> 00:28:55.310
Dr. Lin, you're so serious.

00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:57.240
I

00:28:57.240 --> 00:28:58.960
hate it when people reject my gifts.

00:28:59.110 --> 00:29:00.480
If you truly don't like it,

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:02.350
give it to someone else

00:29:02.640 --> 00:29:04.070
or just throw it away.

00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:05.400
I can't do that either.

00:29:07.110 --> 00:29:07.950
How about this then?

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:08.920
Reciprocate with a gift.

00:29:09.160 --> 00:29:10.790
What do you want? I'll get it for you.

00:29:11.550 --> 00:29:12.440
Let me think.

00:29:16.640 --> 00:29:18.550
Seems like I don't really need anything.

00:29:19.640 --> 00:29:21.480
Not sure what I want right now.

00:29:23.070 --> 00:29:23.960
Besides,

00:29:24.720 --> 00:29:26.680
some things I'm not sure

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:28.070
if you can give.

00:29:28.350 --> 00:29:29.200
Like what?

00:29:33.440 --> 00:29:34.680
Let's keep it a mystery for now.

00:29:35.160 --> 00:29:36.880
I'll tell you when I figure it out.

00:29:39.200 --> 00:29:40.550
Don't regret it then.

00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:43.310
I'll try my best.

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:46.480
Come on, the movie's about to start.

00:29:46.830 --> 00:29:47.670
Let's go.

00:30:05.030 --> 00:30:05.870
It's so hot.

00:30:11.880 --> 00:30:12.830
What are you doing?

00:30:13.070 --> 00:30:14.480
You smell like another guy.

00:30:19.550 --> 00:30:21.030
What? Upset?

00:30:26.900 --> 00:30:31.140
♪I really, really love you♪

00:30:33.180 --> 00:30:34.860
♪That's why I get so jealous♪

00:30:34.880 --> 00:30:35.960
Don't be jealous, okay?

00:30:36.550 --> 00:30:37.960
I'll buy you a watch next time.

00:30:37.960 --> 00:30:38.800
You understand?

00:30:40.830 --> 00:30:42.920
Is it the watch I care about?

00:30:43.640 --> 00:30:45.440
If you're this miserable
hanging out with me,

00:30:45.440 --> 00:30:46.640
then don't come next time, okay?

00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:49.510
I'm just scared you'll get hurt, Sis.

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:51.440
If someone takes advantage of you,

00:30:51.440 --> 00:30:52.920
can you protect yourself?

00:30:53.480 --> 00:30:55.240
He's not that kind of person.

00:30:55.550 --> 00:30:56.390
No need to worry.

00:30:56.720 --> 00:30:58.550
First friends, then like a sister.

00:30:58.680 --> 00:31:00.350
And eventually a little babe.

00:31:00.550 --> 00:31:01.790
It's all part of the act.

00:31:05.790 --> 00:31:07.550
Ugh, I invite you and you're upset.

00:31:07.550 --> 00:31:08.880
I don't invite you and you worry.

00:31:08.880 --> 00:31:10.240
So tell me, what do you want?

00:31:10.480 --> 00:31:11.590
What can I do?

00:31:12.400 --> 00:31:14.200
Better upset than worried.

00:31:14.480 --> 00:31:15.510
Gonna keep enduring.

00:31:18.350 --> 00:31:19.720
But I have to warn you,

00:31:20.200 --> 00:31:22.000
you're not the same as before now.

00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:23.750
If something happens to you,

00:31:23.880 --> 00:31:25.270
the one most heartbroken is Bei.

00:31:26.070 --> 00:31:27.790
I've been quietly
watching over you for him.

00:31:27.960 --> 00:31:30.160
Gonna hand you over
safe and sound.

00:31:33.880 --> 00:31:35.550
